{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2430afac-dc96-4cbc-9894-20e1d90d1c75","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/views.py`:\n\n**`datetime.now()` — line 3**\n```\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is a classic untestable static. `datetime.now()` is hard to mock because it's called directly on the class. It also returns a naive (timezone-unaware) datetime, which Django discourages.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` instead — it's timezone-aware **and** easy to freeze in tests with `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThat's the only static call in the project. The codebase is small — just the one file. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e577fd61-9024-44d3-964a-830c167b852f","outputTokens":211,"requestId":"7C27:6CF89:176C7AC:1AB52F2:69F95C85"},"id":"9dd4f8c0-1ab4-4250-8824-593498f9f975","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:57:17.178Z","parentId":"231f8027-7952-4dc7-ba42-182694151c31"}
